<title>LATVIA: LATVIA-CENTRAL BANK CUTS REFINANCING RATE.</title>
<headline>LATVIA-CENTRAL BANK CUTS REFINANCING RATE.</headline>
<dateline>RIGA 1997-04-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>The central bank said on Tuesday it has decided to cut its refinancing rate to five percent a year from six percent.</p>
<p>The further rate cut is part of the bank's policy of reducing interest rates to stimulate lending.</p>
<p>It also said in a statement that it has cut the lombard rate to six percent for the first 10 days, seven percent for the following 10 days and eight percent for the remaining 10 days.</p>
<p>The length of the repo credit was also extended to 28 days from 10 days, the bank added.</p>
<p>-- Riga Newsroom, +371 721 5240</p>
